Manchester United have reportedly offered defender, Marcos Rojo and 60million euros to Sporting Lisbon for their midfielder, Bruno Fernandes. This was disclosed by respected transfer expert and sports journalist, Nicolo Schira, who works for Gazzetta dello Sport. Schira made this known in a tweet on his official Twitter page on Saturday. He wrote: “Manchester United are in very advanced talks and want to close for Bruno Fernandes. “Red Devils have offered to Sporting €60M + Marcos Rojo on loan. “For Bruno is ready a contract until 2025 with a wages of €6M plus bonuses a year. transfers MUFC.” DAILY POST had reported that Man United were interested in signing Fernandes last summer. But Fernandes ended up staying at Sporting and even signed a new deal last November.